com.bigdata.bop.engine

Class LocalNativeChunkMessage

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.bigdata.bop.engine.LocalNativeChunkMessage
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IChunkMessage<IBindingSet>, IOpMessage, Serializable

    public class LocalNativeChunkMessage
extends Object
implements IChunkMessage<IBindingSet>
    A chunk of intermediate results stored on the native heap which are ready to be consumed by some BOp in a specific query.

    Note: This class is only used in query evaluation for the standalone database.

    See Also:
    Vector query engine on native heap., Serialized Form

      • isLastInvocation

        public boolean isLastInvocation()
        Description copied from interface: IChunkMessage
        Return true iff the IChunkMessage is for the last evaluation pass of an operator. The last evaluation pass for an operator must be requested using an annotation. When it is requested, the operator will be invoked one more time for each node or shard on which it was run (depending on the BOpEvaluationContext). When so invoked, the IChunkMessage will be associated with an empty source and this flag will be set.
        Specified by:
        isLastInvocation in interface IChunkMessage<IBindingSet>
        See Also:
        PipelineOp.Annotations#LAST_PASS
